# 2. Methodology

## Research Design
This study employs a qualitative approach, analyzing textual sources and case studies to explore the principles of Tzedakah and its economic implications. The research draws upon various commentaries from Rishonim and Achronim to provide a comprehensive view.

## Data Collection
Data will be gathered from:
- Historical texts and commentaries on Tzedakah.
- Empirical studies on charitable giving within Jewish communities.
- Interviews and surveys with community leaders and scholars.

## Analysis
The analysis will focus on:
- Comparing halachic obligations with modern economic practices.
- Examining the impact of demographic factors on charitable behaviors.
- Developing models based on the collected data to propose optimal allocations of Tzedakah funds.
